# Intelligence Presentation

- Keep the featured briefing point full-width; arrange points 2–5 in a responsive two-column grid. Size each row from its content and stretch both cards in that row to the same height; do not use a fixed minimum height.
- Briefing-point titles must state the concrete conclusion; never display placeholders such as “要点 1”. Keep linked-signal counters such as `1/5` on the title row, and use at least 15px body text for comfortable reading.
- Use the same 20px title and 16px body typography on briefing points 1–5 so visual hierarchy does not change by rank.
- Keep briefing titles on one line whenever possible. Arrange four reference-number chips as a compact 2×2 grid; shrink chips before wrapping the title. If wrapping is unavoidable, deliberately split the title so the first line is shorter than the second.
- Signal cards must use an accurate Chinese headline as the primary bold title. Preserve the original-language headline as secondary provenance text.
- Prefer an image extracted from the exact article through RSS, Open Graph, or article content. If unavailable, web-search the exact article, named entity, product, or event and use a clearly relevant real-world image. Do not use generic “AI brain/circuit” illustrations or purely AI-generated imagery for unrelated subjects.
- Do not repeat an image URL within one briefing. Deduplicate before rendering and choose a distinct subject-matched real-photo fallback when necessary; never bind real signals to stale rank-based demo images.
- Persist `中文标题` and `图片链接` in Bitable so the card, webpage, and detail view share the same source of truth.
- Every event-aggregation source label must be a working link to that source's corresponding original article. Do not render invented source rows without URLs.
- Initially show a concise subset of “全部信号” and place a clear “查看更多” control below the cards to progressively reveal the remaining filtered results.
- The generated brief should normally retain up to 30 ranked signals so “查看更多” has meaningful depth; the initial viewport may still show only a small subset.
- Treat “内部文档” as its own source category, separate from “实验室”. Demonstrate multiple internal Feishu source forms, including cloud documents, spreadsheets, multidimensional tables, and knowledge bases.
- Every “与我相关” card must expose concrete matching evidence, including at least one related internal document and one tracked topic, entity, source, or trend.
- Render matching evidence as distinct colored blocks. Internal-document evidence links to the data-source panel; tracked-trend evidence links to the “动向追踪” task view. Keep relevance-card titles and explanations visually prominent, and do not show generic instructional copy beneath the section heading.
- In a two-column briefing, never leave a final orphan slot: when the total bullet count is even, promote the last bullet to a full-width featured card.
- Personalized cards use the real signal summary as body copy; keep document/trend evidence on one compact row with complete labels and truncated values.
- Keep all “与我相关” cards equal-height: align their evidence footers to one baseline and vertically center each title/summary block in the remaining space between the fixed header and footer.
- Show 10 signal cards by default and only render progressive disclosure when more than 10 exist. Seed non-empty demo discussion threads for every signal without overwriting user comments.
- Do not show ordinary article images in full-text details. Only place figures extracted from the paper's arXiv/PDF content inside research-paper details; keep supported video embeds in video reading mode and omit media blocks when no source media exists.
- Keep real news fields traceable to Bitable; comments, notes, meetings, and other explicitly mocked interactions may remain local demo data.
